LNB_GENUS.Description: Encoded Value, Genus is a family of related tests. The Letter N-back test displays sequences of uppercase letters. In the 0-back condition, participants respond to a single target (i.e., X). In the 1-back condition they respond if the letter is identical to that preceding it. In the 2-back condition, they respond if the letter is identical to that presented two trials back (Gur et al., 2001; Gur et al., 2010); Ragland et al, 2002).

PCET_GENUS.LongName: PCET: Penn Conditional Exclusion Test Genus
PCET_GENUS.Description: Encoded Value, Genus is a family of related tests. The Penn Conditional Exclusion Test presents four objects at a time, and the participant selects the object that does not belong with the other three based on one of three sorting principles. Sorting principles change, and feedback guides their identification (Gur et al., 2010; Kurtz et al., 2004).

PLOT_GENUS.LongName: PLOT: Penn Line Orientation Test Genus
PLOT_GENUS.Description: Encoded Value, Genus is a family of related tests. The Penn Line Orientation Test presents two lines at an angle, and participants click on a button that makes one line rotate until it has the same angle as the other. The relative location of the lines and their sizes differ across trials (Gur et al., 2010).

Levels.PLOT12: Penn Line Orientation Test with 12 Total Test Trials that rotate 6 degrees per mouse click
